headline: CoreWeave expands OpenAI pact with new $6.5 billion contract
summary: (Reuters) -AI cloud provider CoreWeave has expanded its partnership with OpenAI in a new deal worth up to $6.5 billion, bringing the total value of their agreements to $22.4 billion, the latest in a series of billion-dollar deals OpenAI has signed to secure computational power.  The company behind ChatGPT struck an initial cloud deal with CoreWeave in March worth up to $11.9 billion, followed by a $4 billion add‑on in May.  The latest addition shows the deepening relationship between the two companies as OpenAI seeks multiple partners to help with an unprecedented datacenter buildout to meet its growing computational demands.
